	<div class="What we Treat" id="WhatweTreat?">
	<h2>What we Treat?</h2>
	Modern dermatology encompasses both aspects - Disease and Desire. 
	At City Hospital, we strive to provide a balanced blend of treatment and the cosmetic aspects of skin.
	The dermatologists of City Hospital are experts in successfully treating all 
	 forms of skin-related disfigurements including :-<br>
		<ul type="square">
		<li> Melanomas
		<li> Acne
		<li> Lupus
		<li> Bullous Pemphigoid 
		<li>Eczema
		<li>Psoriasis
		<li>Leprosy
		<li>Infections
		<li>Hair loss
		<li>Skin Cancer
		<li>Vitiligo
		<li>Stevens-Johnson Syndrome
		<li>Pemphigus Vulgaris
		</ul>
	</div>
	<br><br>
	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	At City Hospital division of Dermatology, each patient is treated as per individual analysis 
	as per individual analysis to detect the root cause before the treatment begins.
In addition to our daily outpatient services, the department also carries out diagnostic 
and cosmetic procedures like skin biopsies, electrocautery for removal of skin tags, 
warts curettage of molluscum contagiosum, chemical peels for pigmentation and scars, 
treatment of acne scars, dermaroller for scars, ear piercing, cryotherapy for warts, 
corns, intralesional injections for keloids, patchy hair loss, patch testing and allergy testing. 
In case of dermatological emergencies like Stevens-Johnson Syndrome and Pemphigus Vulgaris, 
the department provides care in the inpatient or ICU setting.
